Big Brand 100 customers switch each way
Small Brand
More of the small brand's customer base turns over.
summary_markdown: This data depicts a customer switching dynamic between a "Big Brand" and a "Small Brand." The core relationship is a bidirectional customer flow, with "100 customers switch each way" indicating an equal number of customers moving from the Big Brand to the Small Brand and vice-versa. The structure highlights a comparative aspect, contrasting the customer base turnover rates. Specifically, the Small Brand experiences a higher proportion of its customer base switching away, implying a greater churn rate for the smaller entity compared to the larger one. This suggests a competitive landscape where the Small Brand, despite receiving customers from the Big Brand, struggles with customer retention.
